# Step 9 — argN out-of-range warning (U9)
# Run as: ./tri run tests/test_arg_warning.tri 42
#
# argc=1, arg0=42, arg1 and arg2 are absent.
# Accessing arg0 (defined): prints 42, no warning.
# Accessing arg1 (missing): warning to stderr + returns 0.
# Accessing arg2 via ?? (coalesce): silent, no warning, prints 99.

arg0 -> emt
arg1 -> emt
arg2 ?? 99 -> emt
